<2ND_LINE>PM-Six Killed,0159</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Six Killed When Pickup Truck Collides With Van</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORSYTH, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pickup truck swerved out of control and
collided with a van on a rain-slick highway in southwest Missouri,
killing six people, authorities said.
   The pickup truck driven by Mary Anne Bristol, 22, of Ava,
skidded out of control Thursday afternoon on U.S. 160 one mile east
of Forsyth, said Trooper Ed Lugenbell of the Missouri State Highway
Patrol.
   After sliding sideways at the crest of a hill, the truck
collided with a van driven by Lawrence Allner, 71, of Sioux City,
Iowa, the patrol said.
   Killed in the accident was Allner, who was driving alone,
Bristol and four passengers riding in the cab of the pickup truck,
the patrol said.
   The dead passengers were Dakota Bristol, 3, of Ava; Carleen
Coombs, 18, of Ava; Mandy Whittenhall, 17, of Ava; and her sister,
Joy Whittenhall, 12, of Ava, authorities said.
</TEXT>
