<2ND_LINE>PM-CVN--Quotes,210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Comments On The Presidential Campaign</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments on the presidential
race as the Republicans wound up their national convention in New
Orleans.
   
   GEORGE BUSH, accepting the presidential nomination of his party:
``There are a lot of great stories in politics about the underdog
winning _ and this is going to be one of them. I mean to run hard,
to fight hard, to stand on the issues _ and I mean to win.''
   
   DAN QUAYLE, alluding to the controversy over his military
service: ``As a young man, I served six years in the National
Guard, and, like millions of Americans who have served in the Guard
and who serve today _ and I am proud of that.''
   
   REP. BOB DORNAN of California, saying Quayle must act swiftly to
diffuse the controversy over his military service: ``It requires a
Checkers-like speech, and he must do _ must do it _ quickly, before
this gets out of hand.''
   
   LEO NADEAU, the vice president's tail-gunner when Bush was a
Navy bomber pilot during World War II, plugging Bush for president:
``When we elect our next commander-in-chief, we will have made sure
he is someone who has the courage and experience we can depend on
for our lives and our livelihoods.''
</TEXT>
