<HEAD>Stocks Up, Dollar Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices firmed in Tokyo trading Friday, while
the dollar lost some ground.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, the main index
of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, closed at 28,209.42 points, up 80.06
points, or 0.28 percent, from Thursday's close.
   On the foreign exchange market, the dollar closed at 133.40 yen,
down 0.53 yen from Thursday's close, after ranging between 133.15
yen and 133.50 yen.
   An exchange dealer at a Tokyo bank said, on condition of
anonymity, there was a strong ``wait-and-see mood'' in the foreign
exchange market.
</TEXT>
