<2ND_LINE>PM-Poland-Glance, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0435,0334</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Poland's Strikes At a Glance</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: ADDS latest mine strike.</NOTE>
<HEAD>With PM-Poland, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a look at the strikes under way in
Poland:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   July Manifesto Mine _ Workers declared an occupation strike
Tuesday at the mine, one of the nation's key producers of
high-grade export coal. The mine, which employs 9,000 workers near
the town of Jastrzebie, was a hotbed of labor activism in the wave
of strikes in 1980 that spawned Solidarity. Up to 5,000 people were
taking part, according to Solidarity, but a management spokesman
put the number at 800-900.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Morcinek Mine _ The first of other mines to strike in support of
July Manifesto. About 400 workers were occupying the mine yard near
the Czech border, Solidarity said.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Andaluzja Mine _ An estimated 2,000 workers occupied the mine
late Wednesday, Solidarity said. The mine is about 42 miles
northeast of the four other mines closed in Silesia near the town
of Piekary Slaskie.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Moszczenica Mine _ About 1,000 workers occupied the mine near
Jastrzebie late Wednesday, according to the union. Management
estimates the number at half that. The mine is one of Poland's
largest, employing 11,000 people.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Jastrzebie Mine _ Workers went on strike Thursday at the mine
near Jastrzebie that employs 8,400 people, management said.
Solidarity supporters estimated 1,500 participants.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   The Port of Szczecin _ Dockworkers went on strike Wednesday in
Poland's second-largest Baltic Sea port. According to Solidarity,
2,000 strikers have brought cargo loading operations to a
standstill.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Transport in Szczecin _ Bus drivers walked off the job Thursday
in support of the coal mine and harbor strikes, causing havoc in
public transport. Solidarity activists estimated 600 people were
taking part.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   30th Anniversary of the People's Poland Mine _ Miners went on
strike today at the mine in the Silesia region. Solidarity
supporters estimated 1,000 workers were involved.
</TEXT>
