<HEAD>Cold Front Causes Rain, Lowers Temps.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A cold front plodded across central and eastern sections of the
nation today, lowering temperatures and scattering rain and
thunderstorms.
   Rain ranged from southern Iowa and northern Missouri through the
upper Ohio Valley to northeastern North Carolina.
   Another cold front caused showers and thunderstorms in eastern
Montana and northwestern North Dakota.
   Elsewhere, showers and thunderstorms were scattered from western
Kansas to eastern New Mexico; from Arkansas to Kentucky; and across
southern Florida.
   Fair skies prevailed across most of the rest of the nation.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms scattered
from the mid-Atlantic Coast through the lower Ohio and middle
Mississippi valleys, Oklahoma and Arkansas, the lower Mississippi
Valley and Gulf Coast into Florida; Showers and thunderstorms
scattered across southeast Colorado, eastern New Mexico, the Texas
Panhandle and central Arizona.
   Highs were expected to be in the 70s from the Great Lakes into
New England and along the Pacific Coast; between 100 and 110 from
the Desert Southwest into the valleys of California; and in the 80s
or 90s across much of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 39
degrees at Houlton, Maine, to 94 at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 79 fair; Boston 59 fair; Buffalo 54 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C., 76 fair; Cincinnati 77 cloudy; Cleveland 58 rain;
Detroit 63 cloudy; Miami 81 showery; New York 65 fair; Philadelphia
70 fair; Pittsburgh 66 showery; Portland 56 fair; Washington 77
shower.
   _Central: Bismarck 62 fair; Chicago 73 cloudy; Dallas-Fort Worth
81 fair; Denver 64 fair; Des Moines 73 partly cloudy; Indianapolis
74 hazy; Kansas City 77 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 67 cloudy;
Nashville 82 fair; New Orleans 75 fair; St. Louis 81 hazy.
   _West: Albuquerque 69 partly cloudy; Anchorage 57 fair; Las
Vegas 90 fair; Los Angeles 62 fair; Phoenix 94 fair; Salt Lake City
67 fair; San Diego 64 cloudy; San Francisco 57 fair; Seattle 57
fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 54 fair; Toronto 54 partly cloudy.
