<FILEID>AP-NR-08-19-88 1158EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Karajan     08-19 0299</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Karajan,0309</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Berlin Conductor Suffers Circulatory Problems</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALZBURG, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Berlin Philharmonic conducter Herbert
von Karajan suffered blood circulation problems and was unable to
conduct tonight at the annual Salzburg cultural festival,
organizers said.
   In a statement issued to news organizations, festival organizers
said ``extreme climatic conditions'' gave the 80-year-old conductor
``a massive circulatory weakness of a dangerous extent.''
   Festival spokesman Hans Widrich said von Karajan was resting at
his home in Anif, a Salzburg suburb, on doctor's orders.
   Asked whether the maestro was conscious, Widrich said, ``Of
course, he asked that the press statement (about the cancellation)
be read to him.''
   He cited ``the great heat which causes problems for many people,
above all for those who are not that young any more.''
   ``Secondly, it is very hot in the festival hall and there is no
air conditioning in the orchestra pit. It is for that reason that
the doctor did not allow Mr. von Karajan'' to conduct Mozart's
opera Don Giovanni tonight.
   Widrich said organizers were confident von Karajan, who ranks
among the world's top conductors, would be able to direct scheduled
concerts with the Berlin Philharmonic in Salzburg Aug. 27 and 28.
   He also expressed some hope that von Karajan might conduct at
least one of two other Don Giovanni performances scheduled for next
week, when the weather is expected to be cooler.
   Von Karajan, the ``director for life'' of the the Berlin
Philharmonic and Salzburg's second most famous son after Mozart,
has conducted regularly at the Salzburg festival since 1948.
   He has been in frail health after years of illness. He also has
had trouble walking to the podium because of serious back problems.
   Organizers said von Karajan's longtime assistant, Bruno Weil,
would direct the Mozart opera at the Salzburg Festival House
tonight.
</TEXT>
