<HEAD>Most New York Beachs Open For Weekend</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   All New York City beaches were expected to be
open this weekend, except one beach on Staten Island, which was
closed Friday because of a high bacterial count, the city said.
   All beaches at federal parks in the New York area also were open.
   Health departments of Long Island to the east and Westchester
County to the north said their state and town beaches also were
open, but some local beaches or lakes with high levels of bacterial
pollution were closed.
   New York area beaches have been closed off and on during the
summer because of medical waste washing onto shores. The problem
also has occurred in other parts of the East Coast.
