<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Hog's Breath,0226</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dirty Harry's Restaurant Kitchen Closed _ Too Dirty</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARMEL, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dirty Harry's restaurant was a little too
dirty, according to health inspectors who closed the kitchen at
Clint Eastwood's Hog's Breath Inn.
   Monterey County environmental health director Walter Wong said
his inspectors found violations ``too numerous to list'' when they
visited the restaurant Thursday.
   The bar remains open.
   Inspectors found inadequate refrigeration, unsanitary
conditions, improper food storage, structural problems that made it
difficult to clean the restaurant and an ``extremely dirty''
kitchen, Wong said.
   ``The dangerous part was the refrigeration was not working,'' he
said. ``Food is supposed to be kept at 40 degrees. This was at 68
degrees.''
   The restaurant's manager was in a meeting and was not available
for comment on Friday, and Eastwood, who is part owner, also was
not available, according to a woman who answered the phone at the
restaurant.
   Eastwood, best known as the tough-talking ``Dirty Harry'' of the
silver screen, was as mayor of this chic hamlet-by-the-sea until
April.
   Wong said the restaurant has been cited before, but corrected
the problems ``enough to get by on.''
   `I really couldn't justify letting them remain open when I felt
there wa a potential for people getting sick,'' said Updike. ``I
think they pretty much agreed with us.''
