<HEAD>Human Rights Officials Barred from Checking on Colleague</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GENEVA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Romania has refused to let a United Nations human
rights panel examine Romania's treatment of one of the panel's own
special investigators, a U.N. official said.
   The East European nation barred entrance to two members of the
panel who were hoping to meet with Dumitru Mazilu, a Romanian
colleague who recently resigned, said U.N. Under-Secretary General
for Human Rights Jan Martenson Wednesday.
