   The Navy's sophisticated Aegis air defense
system worked properly in the shooting down of an Iranian
commercial airliner last month, a Pentagon review as their convoy left
Baghdad.
Their posts were on the 730 miles of border that begins in the
southern marshlands and snakes north to the rugged mountains of
Kurdistan.
   Iran continued to question Iraq's motives. Hashemi Rafsanjani,
parliament speaker and military commander, said the Iraqis may not
want peace but will find Iran much stronger if they renew the war.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>HUNTINGTON, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sen. Dan Quayle insisted Friday that he
broke no rules to get into the Indiana National Guard fairly during
the Vietnam War, but acknowledged that he sought help from a former
guard commander who worked for his grandfather and assumes calls
were made on his behalf.
   The Republican vice presidential nominee said he would do the
same thing again.
   At a news conference at his hometown, Quayle portrayed the chain
of events leading to his enrollment in the Guard as normal given
his relationship with his family and their friends.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   They were relegated to supporting roles, but
some lesser known Republican faces were given convention exposure
this week and can be counted among the party's leaders for the
future.
   Names like Phil Gramm, who described himself as doing ``the
Lord's work in the devil's city.'' And Olympia Snowe, who wielded
the gavel with humor and aplomb. And Tom Kean, who scored the
Democrats for ``pastel patriotism.''
   Political conventions are expected to make and end political
careers, and this one made Dan Quayle what George Bush said he was:
one of the party's ``rising young stars.''
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>BEIT SAHUR, Occupied West Bank (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Leaders of local committee
said Friday they will defy Israeli attempts to stamp out the
informal system of self-rule that has sprung up during the
8-month-old Palestinian uprising.
   Defense Minister Yitzhak Rabin declared the ``popular
committees'' illegal on Thursday and threatened to deport prominent
