   The only agreement reached was to hold a second meeting Saturday.
   Five lawmakers from each country ended Friday's nearly
three-hour meeting at this truce village 35 miles north of Seoul
without any agreement, but the second session could clear the way
for full talks on the Sept. 17-Oct. 2 Olympics and a non-aggression
pact proposed by North Korea.
