<TEXT>
   A feeble Wall Street advance fizzled on profit-taking Thursday.
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 1.07 gain to 2,027.03.
   The dollar fell as major central banks entered the market to
push the U.S. currency lower.
   Bond prices rose slightly in quiet trading.
   Coffee futures prices rose sharply; frozen pork belly futures
soared; most livestock futures gained; copper and precious metals
moved up; crop and energy futures were mostly higher; and
stock-index futures advanced.
