<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Britain-Inflation     08-19 0122</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Inflation,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Annual Rate Rises to 4.8 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Britain's annual inflation rate rose to 4.8
percent in July from 4.6 percent in the previous month, the
government reported Friday.
   The retail price index rose 0.1 percent in July after a 0.4
percent rise in June, the Department of Employment said.
   The retail price index, which uses a January 1987 basis of 100,
stood at 106.7 in July, up from 106.6 in June, and up from 101.8 in
July 1987.
   The latest rise in the index was mainly due to higher prices for
cars, insurance, non-seasonal foods, electricity and gas, the
department said.
   As is usual for the season, prices for fresh food and clothing
were lower, it said.
</TEXT>
