<1ST_LINE>u f PM-WallStreet10am     08-19 0190</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street 10am,0204</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market opened slightly higher this
morning in slow trading, echoing a trendless pattern that has
affected Wall Street all week.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrial stocks was up 9.42 points
to 2,036.45 by 10 a.m. EDT.
   Among broader market indicators, the New York Stock Exchange
composite index of all listed issues rose 0.51 to 148.32. The
American Stock Exchange market-value index rose 0.27 to 295.23.
   Gaining issues outnumbered advances by more than a 5-to-3 margin
on the NYSE, with 574 up, 296 down and 441 unchanged. Volume
totaled 15.12 million shares after the first 30 minutes.
   Stock analysts said they did not expect a significant move
either way in prices today, attributing the sluggishness to the
lack of economic news and an underlying investor apathy about the
market.
   On Thursday, the Dow Jones industrials rose 1.07 points to
2,027.03.
   Advancing issues outnumbered declines by about a 7-to-6 margin
in nationwide trading of NYSE-listed stocks, with 740 issues up,
644 down and 587 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 139.82 million shares, vs. 169.50
million in the previous session.
</TEXT>
