<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Switzerland-Unemployment     08-19 0113</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Switzerland-Unemployment,0120</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>BERN, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unemployment in Switzerland, already
the lowest in the industralized West, dropped to a six-year low
last month while the number of vacant positions reached a
seven-year-high, authorities announced Friday.
   The Federal Office for Industry and Labor said that a total of
20,963 jobless were registered in July, an 8.7 percent drop from
the previous month.
   The office said this was the lowest figure since October 1982.
The unemployment rate remained at 0.7 percent.
   Vacant full-time jobs totaled 13,987 the highest since 1981.
Klaus Hug, director of the labor office, said unemployment now had
reached about its bottom level and that no further spectacular
decline was expected.
