<HEAD>London Share Prices Rise</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: UPDATES throughout with close.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices rose Friday as a handful of food
manufacturing and engineering stocks led the market higher.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed up
10.4 points, or 0.6 percent, at 1,844.3.
   Volume was a light 342.4 million shares, up from 335.2 million
shares Thursday.
   Dealers said the overall tone of the market remained firm, but
they noted there was little specific news to drive individual share
prices.
   ``There weren't many sellers around, so the market followed its
recent tendency to move higher,'' one dealer said.
   The market showed virtually no reaction to Friday's release of
the British government's latest report on retail prices, which
matched market expectations. Retail prices rose 0.1 percent in July
from the previous month and 4.8 percent from the year-ago period.
   In the afternoon, London share prices got a boost from Wall
Street, where the Dow Jones average of 30 industrials moved higher.
</TEXT>
