<TEXT>
   The stock market trudged to a slightly higher
finish today in some of the lightest trading of the year, capping a
dreary week of investor apathy and confusion about where prices are
going.
   ``The market's been closed for the week,'' said Robert Meyer,
director of research at the Fahnestock & Co. investment firm in New
York. ``I think there's a general lack of confidence in the market,
particularly because of uncertanty over the economy and direction
of interest rates.''
   With short-term Treasury bonds offering relatively high rates of
interest, brokers said, there's not much inclination for investors
to risk their money in stocks.
